# The build context is ./frontend, so the REPO-ROOT .dockerignore does not apply here — Docker only
# reads the one at the context root. Without this file, `COPY . .` copied the HOST's node_modules into
# the image: it overwrote the clean `npm ci` install (shipping glibc binaries into an alpine image),
# re-introduced the LGPL `sharp` blobs we deliberately removed, and meant whatever happened to be on a
# developer's laptop got baked into a published artifact. A build must depend on the lockfile, not on
# the machine that ran it.
node_modules
.next
out
*.tsbuildinfo
.env
.env.local
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
